You might as well have a murderer going around with a duster and binoculars and a murder bag or something.
Or maybe we can just keep costumes as they are, rogues wearing their already compromised clothes when they’ve left the “real” world behind.
If you are a werewolf, when you turn on the moon and get dressed in wolf skins, and return to being human again, do you stay dressed in wolf skins but put on some lighter clothing? Do you just wear nothing at all and shrug it off? I really think I don’t want to know the answer over any of these.
The shark with no fin (also a Christmas carol), the ghost dressed as Michael Myers, why wear clothes, ever?
What’s worse than bunnies coming out of an Easter basket? Pesach killing King Herod’s rabbits.

Why did she have to shoot her so hard, the sheriff thought as she nursed her hand. It’ll be a week before I can make arrangements to get in and out of my boots myself without someone’s help. When she got up on Tuesday morning, her boots were unnervingly too tight. The old cow byre was dark, but it was the easiest cow byre to get in and out of out of all of them now. She made it there with the aid of a porch step stool. 
Her chest pushed tightly into the leather of her shirt and the cups of her bra were constricted to the point that they buckled at the seams. She groaned audibly. Getting it on and off, off and on had been a chore that defeated the central benefit of body padding — self defense. A little sigh that sounded like a contented horse shook her belly as she pushed on her boots. She read in complete aloud to hurtling deer “the virgin white liquid milk that has been kept uncontaminated on the mother’s skin, his highest lodging-place, being, as we have seen, its fountain and primer”. The only milk she had been constrained to keep away on her body had not been a very pleasant thing, Polly’s 40% cream puff had felt so much more comforting than natural breastmilk. 
The sheriff did her shoes up and took two pointed practice steps forward. Her belly rubbed outwards on the gun she wore on her belly with each stop and she made up skipped two small steps of those instead to avoid the pressure. When she got back to the kitchen she was achy in the most unusual places, chafed in her groin and between her legs, and her back hurt from heaving out platters of cinnamon buns. These sexy high heeled boots that she had convinced the PTA to get her for the fun run at the 5k festival . . . hurt like hell when she wore them. It was next to impossible to get her wool socks up her hog-tied, strung up , blown up thighs but they did help with the chafing and the swollen skin around her legs was as hard as crags now.
